<h1 style="color:black;margin-top:10px;margin-left:245">The USDA Food Pyramid</h1>

<div style="margin-top:12px;margin-left:70px">
<img src="http://boston.lti.cs.cmu.edu/Services/clueweb12_render/getresource.cgi/getresource.cgi?id=38C004C78124B1C31D31FAC1AE7D9F0BEC219446" alt="Okinawa Diet Food Pyramid"  />
</div>

<div style="margin-left:106px;width:550px;font-weight:bold;text-align:left;font-size:11px">
The USDA food pyramid is currently undergoing revision. Critics claim the pyramid gives misleading information
on serving and portion sizes and does not disinguish between healthy and non-healthy fats and carbohydrates. Also, omega-3 
and flavonoid rich foods like fish and beans should be seperated from red meats.
</div>

